Kostki is an abandoned village in the administrative district of Gmina Górowo Iławeckie, in Bartoszyce County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland.
From 1945 to 1958 Kostki was administratively located in the Iławka County in the Masurian District and Olsztyn Voivodeship.
